She looked at Scorponok. "Oh, I was in the lab fixing that auto-defence 
system in for you.  I saw a strange black box sitting on your workbench.  Is 
it something for a new system? I didn't touch it, but I'm just curious. If 
it's nothing, then I won't give it a second thought."
She kissed his cheek.  "Your way too good to me."
